To the Constructor: Not meant as a criticism of your skills; it’s a nicely crafted puzzle. It’s just that someone slotted it into the wrong day of the week.

@Barry Ancona
Back in the day when Charles M. Deber was crafting his amazing (tough!) puzzles, there would have been no shading...  and we still managed to solve the puzzles, but not swiftly, not without tearing our hair, not without howls of agony.  
At least, that's how I remember them....

@Hanson

Today took me 13 minutes whereas yesterday took me around 30.  

I can see how yesterday's would have been easier if you consistently watched every movie to be released in the 80s and 90s.  But without knowing the sequel titles by heart you're dealing with trying to piece them together with lots of proper noun/niche trivia crossings and stretch-words like SLEEKEN.

